					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Maṇikaṇṭhēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 1[4]: 985 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete and damaged. It records an endowment made by (Prince) Madhurāntakan Gaṇḍarādittaṉ for the supply of four <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> each of honey, ghee, milk, curd, seasamum, gingelly, blackgram, <hi rend="italic">tiṇai,</hi> sugarcane juice, tender coconut, water, lime, greengram and other materials for the anointment of God as also for the provision of flowers on every <hi rend="italic">saṅkrānthi</hi> day in each month in the temple of Mahādēva at Tirumālpēṟu in Dāmar-kōṭṭam.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 341.</p>						

						</summary>
